<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-064-378 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 215 065</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Sept 2 1991 n436 p137(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Compaq sets Japan strategy.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hubbard, Holly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Compaq will use account managers to make initial contact withpotential customers in Japan, a much more direct approach togenerating sales than the company has taken in either the US orEurope.andP;  Compaq will not sell directly to Japanese customers.andO;Compaq has used a similar strategy in the US and Europe forbreaking into major accounts, but account managers will play aneven greater role in Japan.andP;  The sales strategy will run parallelto the independent efforts of Compaq's Japanese resellers.andP;  Compaqalso will take a more direct approach in providing post-salescustomer support.andP;  An undisclosed number of Japanese systemsengineers have been hired to support Japanese users.andP;  Compaq'sJapanese line is expected to support the DOS/V compatible standardand a Japanese version of Microsoft Windows 3.0.andP;  Compaq is notcommenting on its Japanese line, other to say that it will offer abroad product line.andP;  Insiders believe the company will concentrateits efforts almost completely on Intel 80486-based systems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Compaq Computer Corp. (Planning).andO;Ticker:    CPQ.andO;Topic:     JapanMarket EntrySales ManagementStrategic PlanningDistribution Management.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>